1-5/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:64:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/introducing-layers-1-5/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 28 Apr 2016 08:19:09 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"Layers";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2466";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:399:"<p>It''s been just over a year since we launched Layers and the rate of improvement has not halted. To today we are proud to announce Layers 1.5, the best version of Layers and Layers Pro yet.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/introducing-layers-1-5/">Introducing Layers 1.5</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"David Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6540:"<p>At the beginning of 2016 we pledged to focus on making Layers the <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/">best page builder it could be</a> and with every subsequent version release there have been significant improvements in speed, functionality and flexibility. While we released those updates, we were secretly preparing for the big one, the most significant release of Layers since, well, Layers itself.</p>\n<p>Our focus this year has been to attend to the needs and requests of you, our users, in an effort to make it more flexible while still maintaining the signature world-class usability that has made Layers so popular. We believe we&#8217;ve achieved that and are proud to unleash a bunch of useful new features which take Layers to the next level:</p>\n<h3>A Completely New Grid Structure</h3>\n<p>No longer constrained by static column widths in the Content Widget you&#8217;ll now be able to use varying column sizes when creating new content without having to hack together two widgets. This greatly improves the HTML structure of your page and therefore SEO. It also opens up bunch of new page building opportunities which we&#8217;re excited to show you soon.</p>\n<p>A prime example of the new grid is our fresh home page which has a mixture of column widths used within the same content widget.</p>\n<div id="attachment_2472" style="width: 297px" class="wp-caption alignright"><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/seo-headers-small.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2472"><img class="wp-image-2472 size-full" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/seo-headers-small.png" alt="seo-headers-small" width="287" height="345" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Brand new in Layers Pro is the ability to choose the heading type of widgets and content widget columns.</p></div>\n<h3>Massive SEO improvements</h3>\n<p>The <em>number one</em> request we received from you was more control over the SEO of your Layers site. The biggest challenge we faced though was that no two people could agree on what those better practices were, so we went back to basics and relooked at every line of HTML in Layers.</p>\n<p>So now not only will you have an improved HTML layout (free in Layers) but users of <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/">Layers Pro</a> will now also be able to choose which heading type to use in widgets and content widget columns. This tweak on its own is hugely powerful and will help you determine the exact content hierarchy of your web pages.</p>\n<h3>Parallax Backgrounds</h3>\n<div id="attachment_2476" style="width: 1335px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/parallax.gif" rel="attachment wp-att-2476"><img class="wp-image-2476 size-full" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/parallax.gif" alt="parallax" width="1325" height="832" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Look at it moooooove :)</p></div>\n<p>As we gear up to improve the animations within Layers we are excited to launch a new Parallax background option for users of Layers Pro. The sense of depth you achieve by switching on this feature is awesome and we&#8217;re already using it on our main site.</p>\n<h3>Improved Button Styling Controls</h3>\n<div id="attachment_2481" style="width: 690px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/button-customization.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2481"><img class="wp-image-2481 size-full" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/button-customization.png" alt="button-customization" width="680" height="489" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/button-customization.png 680w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/button-customization-300x216.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Individually style buttons in the slider and content widget without touching a line of code.</p></div>\n<p>Finally with <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/">Layers Pro</a>, you&#8217;ll be able to control the styling of your buttons within the Slider and Content Widget. Options include background color, gradient, borders, border radius and four different choices of button size. All this without needing to touch a line of code.</p>\n<div id="attachment_2482" style="width: 292px" class="wp-caption alignright"><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/content-widget-padding-margin.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2482"><img class="wp-image-2482 size-full" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/content-widget-padding-margin.png" alt="content-widget-padding-margin" width="282" height="368" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/content-widget-padding-margin.png 282w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/content-widget-padding-margin-230x300.png 230w" sizes="(max-width: 282px) 100vw, 282px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">You can now edit padding and margin in individual columns in the Content Widget.</p></div>\n<h3>Greater Content and Slider Widget Customizability</h3>\n<p>The Content Widget has probably gone through some of the biggest improvements in 2016 and we&#8217;re now happy to provide the option of determining the exact padding and margins of each column when creating and editing an existing Layers page.</p>\n<h3>Image resizing</h3>\n<p>As you&#8217;ll see on our site we rely on Icons quite a lot for our look and feel. Up until today we relied on some custom CSS to resize them correctly but from now on <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/">Layers Pro</a> users will be able to do that without touching a line of code with a new resize controller built into the image uploading interface in your Slider and Content Widgets.</p>\n<h3>How to update</h3>\n<p>The new grid and HTML are immediately available in free version of <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/download-layers/" target="_blank">Layers 1.5</a>, simply update via your WordPress dashboard and you&#8217;re good to go. To unlock header selection, parallax, button styling and other new features please be sure to download the latest version of <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/" target="_blank">Layers Pro</a> from your profile on CodeCanyon.net. Enjoy!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/introducing-layers-1-5/">Introducing Layers 1.5</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/introducing-layers-1-5/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"14";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:45:"Layers 1.5 RC1 is Ready For Developer Testing";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:80:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/layers-1-5-rc1-is-ready-for-development-testing/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:88:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/layers-1-5-rc1-is-ready-for-development-testing/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 14 Apr 2016 20:22:54 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Development";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"development";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2455";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:375:"<p>Layers 1.5 is a major release due out at the end of next week which implements several front-end and widget changes.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/layers-1-5-rc1-is-ready-for-development-testing/">Layers 1.5 RC1 is Ready For Developer Testing</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Vail Joy";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1989:"<p>As a result, it is critical for extension and child theme authors to test your products and ensure they are updated for compatibility. Below is an outline of changes that have gone in so far which we anticipate will impact you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Framework updated to use an entirely new grid system using flexbox and calc(). This fixes several issues with column combinations in the Content Widget and allows for better responsiveness.</li>\n<li>Front-end markup adjusted for better HTML5 outlines to improve SEO going forward.</li>\n<li>WordPress post class and post ID tags are set on &lt;articles&gt;</li>\n<li>Added <code>id="post-list"</code> to post archive template containers to allow for easier implementation of list load effects such as infinite scroll.</li>\n<li>Text control moved from widget Design Bar to inline in the Widget Title field for more contextual UX and to support heading tag select in Layers Pro</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Update Your Products</h3>\n<p>Please review all <a href="https://github.com/Obox/layerswp/tree/1-5-rc1">changes on GitHub</a> and go through our <a href="http://docs.layerswp.com/layers-1-5-developer-update-guide/">Layers 1.5 Developer Update Guide</a> for help migrating your changes.</p>\n<p>A <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/download/layers-1-5-rc1/">download link to the Release Candidate</a> is included in the guide. RC1 should only be used for testing purposes. Install on a live site at <strong>your own risk</strong>!</p>\n<h3>Give Us Feedback</h3>\n<p>Please use Layers Messenger to report any major bugs on this release or to get help with updating your product. Please let us know which theme or extension you authored and mention you are testing on RC1 so we can prioritize you faster.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/layers-1-5-rc1-is-ready-for-development-testing/">Layers 1.5 RC1 is Ready For Developer Testing</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:85:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/layers-1-5-rc1-is-ready-for-development-testing/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:38:"WordPress 4.5 “Coleman” and Layers";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/wordpress-4-5-and-layers/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/wordpress-4-5-and-layers/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 12 Apr 2016 15:21:43 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"wordpress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2447";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:439:"<p>WordPress 4.5 has gone live, with hundreds of fixes, changes and tiny improvements. It brings with it a handful of great new features highlighted below, and how they affect your Layers website (or not!)</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/wordpress-4-5-and-layers/">WordPress 4.5 &#8220;Coleman&#8221; and Layers</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Vail Joy";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3750:"<h3>Theme Logos</h3>\n<p>The Customizer now includes Logo selection for all themes, which is already implemented in Layers. While the Logo functionality in Layers will not change for you, you may notice your logo preview is no longer shown after updating to 4.5 (though the logo is showing on your site.) This does not indicate any problem with your logo and is a result of the update to a new logo control &#8211; you need only select it again to reset the preview thumbnail.</p>\n<p>This new control adds an extra Crop step to logo selection, to give you more control over the image. This should help those of you who previously had issues with your logo image being cropped on the sides, or being uploaded with too much white space.</p>\n<h3>Image Performance Improvements</h3>\n<p>Following up on the introduction of responsive images in WordPress 4.4, WordPress 4.5 is making changes to <a href="https://make.wordpress.org/core/2016/03/12/performance-improvements-for-images-in-wordpress-4-5/">improve image performance</a> including improved compression settings and smarter handling of image metadata. This update also fixes an issue where <a href="http://docs.layerswp.com/doc/wordpress-images-dont-load-after-4-4-update-with-ssl-enabled/" target="_blank">Mobile Images Wouldn&#8217;t Load After 4.4 Update on sites with SSL enabled</a></p>\n<h3>Customizer Performance Improvements</h3>\n<p>Live Preview has once again received attention in 4.5 as part of <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/10/what-the-new-wordpress-customizer-roadmap-means-for-layers/" target="_blank">WordPress.org&#8217;s over-arching Roadmap</a>.  The bulk of performance increases comes with widget initialization changes and Selective Refresh implementation, which we have taken full advantage of already and will continue to optimize in the next version of Layers coming this month. <a href="https://make.wordpress.org/core/2016/02/16/selective-refresh-in-the-customizer/">Selective Refresh</a> allows for changes to appear quicker inside the preview, with less code than before. We do not require developers to make any changes to custom widgets which are specific to Selective Refresh. If you have non-Layers widgets in your products, you can find <a href="https://make.wordpress.org/core/2016/03/22/implementing-selective-refresh-support-for-widgets/" target="_blank">instructions for Selective Refresh on the Make WordPress blog</a>.</p>\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\n<p>All in all, 4.5 is an excellent update with tons of added stability and performance enhancements and should not impact your Layers site negatively. To learn more about WordPress 4.5, visit the <a href="https://make.wordpress.org/core/2016/03/30/wordpress-4-5-field-guide/" target="_blank">4.5 Field Guide</a>, or the <a href="http://wptavern.com/tag/wordpress-4-5" target="_blank">WordPress 4.5 roundup</a>,</p>\n<h3>Developers</h3>\n<p>Theme Developers may be especially interested in the <a href="https://make.wordpress.org/core/2016/03/11/embeds-changes-in-wordpress-4-5/" target="_blank">introduction of embed templates</a> to the template hierarchy, which allow you to control and style how oEmbed content looks in posts and pages (note, this does not affect embeds in Widgets).</p>\n<p>Big changes are coming in Layers that will impact your products. To get on our mailing list to ensure you are notified about betas, be sure to <a href="http://oboxthemes.us10.list-manage.com/subscribe?u=5b9a020fcf797987098cc7bca&amp;id=069cfedbbc" target="_blank">sign up here</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/wordpress-4-5-and-layers/">WordPress 4.5 &#8220;Coleman&#8221; and Layers</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/wordpress-4-5-and-layers/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:43:"Industry Conf Tickets: And the winner is…";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/industry-conf-congrats-to-elliot/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/industry-conf-congrats-to-elliot/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 05 Apr 2016 12:38:36 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"competition";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2439";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:391:"<p>Firstly we want to thank everyone for entering our Industry Conf. ticket competition. We hope to do more giveaways like this one during the year.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/industry-conf-congrats-to-elliot/">Industry Conf Tickets: And the winner is&#8230;</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"David Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:726:"<p>We&#8217;d also like to thank <a href="http://2016.industryconf.com/">Industry Conf</a> for allowing us to hold this competition, we wish we could be there ourselves and have no doubt it will be a massive success.</p>\n<p>Without further delay we&#8217;d finally like to announce the winner&#8230;</p>\n<p>Congratulations to Elliot for <a href="https://raison.co/">Raison.co</a>! You are the lucky winner of two tickets to the Industry Conf!</p>\n<p>Enjoy and come back with stories!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/industry-conf-congrats-to-elliot/">Industry Conf Tickets: And the winner is&#8230;</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/04/industry-conf-congrats-to-elliot/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"2";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:38:"Win Two Free Tickets to Industry Conf!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/win-two-free-tickets-to-industry-conference/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:85:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/win-two-free-tickets-to-industry-conference/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 07 Mar 2016 11:19:45 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"competition";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2405";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:399:"<p>Founded by one of Obox''s own, Industry Conf is one of the best web conferences held in the UK and this year we''re giving away two tickets to the event.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/win-two-free-tickets-to-industry-conference/">Win Two Free Tickets to Industry Conf!</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"David Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2214:"<p><a href="http://2016.industryconf.com/">Industry Conf</a> has been running since 2012 and has featured some the web&#8217;s heavyweights, including the Godfather of Web Standards, Jeff Zeldman. Its focus on design and UX is one of the reasons we&#8217;re so excited about it.</p>\n<p>Each year, <a href="https://twitter.com/gavinelliott" target="_blank">Gavin</a> (its founder) goes the extra mile to expand, brighten and make it more engaging, and this year will be no different. In fact back in 2012, we made the trek from South Africa to Newcastle to attend the first event and left with relationships and opportunities that we still have to this day.</p>\n<blockquote><p>At Industry, every year is different. Our Industry moves quickly and I spend months out of every year working with speakers and curating content so that every attendee can get practical takeaways from the day. Every year we meet to learn something new.<br />\n<cite>Gavin Elliott</cite></p></blockquote>\n<p>You can check out the amazing <a href="http://2016.industryconf.com/" target="_blank">speaker list</a> and <a href="http://2016.industryconf.com/" target="_blank">event details</a> here.</p>\n<h3>We&#8217;re giving away two tickets!</h3>\n<p>With the conference now being an established part of the web conference circuit, we have teamed up with Gavin to give away two IndustryConf tickets to this year&#8217;s event, valued at £300.</p>\n<p><strong>To enter is really simple:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Leave a comment on our blog with a reason why you think you should win the free tickets</li>\n<li>Don&#8217;t forget to leave your twitter name in the comment so we can contact when you win</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The winner will be announced on our twitter account next week! Good luck!</p>\n<p><em>Please make sure that you are able to attend the conference on the 20th of April 2016. We really want these tickets to go to someone who is excited and interested by what IndustryConf has to offer.</em></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/win-two-free-tickets-to-industry-conference/">Win Two Free Tickets to Industry Conf!</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:81:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/win-two-free-tickets-to-industry-conference/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"13";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:86:"Our First Theme of 2016 is Live, Say Hello to Crafthouse a WooCommerce Furniture Theme";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:88:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/our-first-theme-of-2016-is-live-say-hello-to-crafthouse/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:96:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/our-first-theme-of-2016-is-live-say-hello-to-crafthouse/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 02 Mar 2016 10:52:20 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2390";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:536:"<p>This one has been a long time in the making but we''re super excited to launch it. Crafthouse is a WooCommerce Furniture Theme designed for the contemporary furniture company looking for a fresh and modern look for their website.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/our-first-theme-of-2016-is-live-say-hello-to-crafthouse/">Our First Theme of 2016 is Live, Say Hello to Crafthouse a WooCommerce Furniture Theme</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"David Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2472:"<p><a href="http://themeforest.net/item/crafthouse-woocommerce-furniture-theme/14542098?ref=obox">Crafthouse</a> has been a project that we&#8217;ve been busy with since December of 2015. A furniture theme designed by an incredibly talented South African, <a href="http://www.ianroblambert.com/">Ian Lambert</a>, we wanted something that fits perfectly into Layers&#8217; ability to create different layouts with the click of a button.</p>\n<p>When Ian presented us with the initial designs we were so happy that we jumped directly into the conversion phase. The result is what you see here, a WooCommerce theme aimed at modern furniture companies who are looking for a fresh look for their website.</p>\n<p><a href="http://themeforest.net/item/crafthouse-woocommerce-furniture-theme/full_screen_preview/14542098?ref=obox" target="_blank" rel="attachment wp-att-2391"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2391" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/crafthouse-screenshots.jpg" alt="crafthouse-screenshots" width="1000" height="339" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/crafthouse-screenshots.jpg 1000w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/crafthouse-screenshots-300x102.jpg 300w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/crafthouse-screenshots-768x260.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></a></p>\n<p>We love it and know you will too with it&#8217;s minimal look, sharp typography and inspiring demo content.</p>\n<p>As with any Layers theme created by our team, we have made sure it works seamlessly with all our plugins and has been tested with all the options available in the free version of Layers. Dynamic header layouts, multiple widgets and the 100&#8217;s of different Content Widget combos have been factored into it&#8217;s design.</p>\n<p>Crafthouse can be bought on Themeforest for $46 and comes packaged with <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/storekit/">StoreKit</a> absolutely free. <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/crafthouse-woocommerce-furniture-theme/full_screen_preview/14542098?ref=obox">Check out the demo</a> and let us know what you think in the comments!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/our-first-theme-of-2016-is-live-say-hello-to-crafthouse/">Our First Theme of 2016 is Live, Say Hello to Crafthouse a WooCommerce Furniture Theme</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:93:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/our-first-theme-of-2016-is-live-say-hello-to-crafthouse/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:41:"Linking just got a lot easier with Layers";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/linking-just-got-a-lot-easier-with-layers/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:83:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/linking-just-got-a-lot-easier-with-layers/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 18 Feb 2016 07:52:50 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Uncategorized";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2231";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:356:"<p>We just dropped a new version of Layers which includes an improved linking interface and the death of FOUC.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/linking-just-got-a-lot-easier-with-layers/">Linking just got a lot easier with Layers</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"David Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2541:"<h3>What the FOUC happened?</h3>\n<p>Flash Of Unstyled Content, which up till now has been a bit of a bugbear with Layers, is no longer an issue. With the release of Layers 1.2.12 we have made some major changes to the way custom CSS is loaded and the result is a much smoother and modern experience for first time visitors to your site.</p>\n<p>No longer will they see a flash of a grey unstyled site, but instead a perfectly format destination just as you designed it. Releasing a fix for this has been something we&#8217;ve been trying to do for a while and are really happy to have it out there now!</p>\n<h3>Linking just got overhauled</h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/dynamic-linking-1212.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2242"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2242" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/dynamic-linking-1212.png" alt="dynamic-linking-1212" width="660" height="760" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/dynamic-linking-1212.png 660w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/dynamic-linking-1212-261x300.png 261w" sizes="(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px" /></a></p>\n<p>Another new feature in Layers 1.2.12 is a brand new linking interface in our content and slider widgets. This massive update makes it much easier (and more dynamic) to link between pages and posts within your site.</p>\n<p>The interface will now allow you to choose between an outbound link or dynamic content within your website. The benefits are huge:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Changing links within your site no longer requires that you go to each Layers page and update hard coded URL&#8217;s.</li>\n<li>By relying on WordPress&#8217; core linking architecture your permalink settings will now automatically apply to the buttons in your sliders and content widget.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Finally, you can now also determine whether or not a link opens in a new window. Happy Days <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/72x72/1f642.png" alt="🙂" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>\n<p>Be sure to update your version of Layers today and get hold of two awesome new features which continue to make Layers the most user friendly <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/">WordPress Site Builder</a> in the World.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/linking-just-got-a-lot-easier-with-layers/">Linking just got a lot easier with Layers</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/linking-just-got-a-lot-easier-with-layers/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"8";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"Layers 1.2.11 Has Just Dropped, Here’s Why You Should Update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:91:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:100:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 04 Feb 2016 13:59:46 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"layers updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2182";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:467:"<p>The latest version of Layers is now live with a brand new Page Revisions feature that will give you piece of mind the next time you make any change to one of your Layers pages.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/">Layers 1.2.11 Has Just Dropped, Here&#8217;s Why You Should Update</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"David Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4690:"<h3>Introducing Page Revisions</h3>\n<p>Having piece of mind while you make changes to your site is important. There is nothing worse than accidentally deleting something you cannot recover and until today that was a scary possibility. We have been so focused on page revisions that we decided to release it before any other new 2016 features (more on that in a moment).</p>\n<p>So what do Page Revisions do? Well now every time you save a page, we will automatically store that as a version that you can revert back to at any point in the future. That means you can make as many changes as you like and should you not like them, you can roll back to a previous version with relative ease.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2193"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2193" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02.png" alt="revisions-02" width="1683" height="880" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02.png 1683w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02-300x157.png 300w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02-768x402.png 768w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02-1024x535.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1683px) 100vw, 1683px" /></a></p>\n<p>In order to roll back all you need to do is go to the &#8220;Edit Page&#8221; section in WordPress, click on the specific page you want to revert and then click on &#8220;Revisions&#8221;. In there you&#8217;ll be presented with a timeline slider that will allow you to easily go back to a different state.</p>\n<p>The knock on affect of this change is equally important as we&#8217;re now storing your content in the same place that SEO plugins look. So from now on, Yoast, All in One SEO etc. are 100% compatible with Layers. It&#8217;s a big deal and one we&#8217;re quite proud of.</p>\n<h4>Some other important changes</h4>\n<p>Along with Page Revisions there have been some other changes on the admin site which you may find important:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>We&#8217;ve split out our admin CSS file into three separate files for easier management across different interfaces.</li>\n<li>The marketplace section has had a <em>complete redesign</em>, making it easier to browse and preview items.</li>\n<li>You can now select a primary color during the onboarding process. No more grey websites!</li>\n</ol>\n<p>So don&#8217;t waste any time and update to Layers 1.2.11 directly from your WordPress dashboard</p>\n<h4>What&#8217;s Next?</h4>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/new-link-interface-01-1.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2190"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2190" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/new-link-interface-01-1.png" alt="new-link-interface-01" width="660" height="710" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/new-link-interface-01-1.png 660w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/new-link-interface-01-1-279x300.png 279w" sizes="(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px" /></a></p>\n<p>With version 1.2.11 live we are already fully focused on the next release, here&#8217;s what you can look forward to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Smart/Dynamic linking &#8211; no more hard coding of page links! This will make it much easier to transfer a site from a dev environment to a live environment.</li>\n<li>Better onboarding &#8211; making Layers easier for new users is a pillar of the product so onboarding will be looked at in Feb.</li>\n<li>New preset page layouts &#8211; we want to expand our preset page layout options.</li>\n<li>New grid system &#8211; this isn&#8217;t guaranteed for the next release but is a huge focus for me (David) as we aim to make our grid layout more flexible.</li>\n<li>New HTML for SEO friendliness &#8211; this was planned for 1.2.11, but has been pushed out.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>One last thing!</h3>\n<p>February marks one year since Layers was <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/02/from-today-the-way-you-build-wordpress-sites-will-change-say-hello-to-layers/">launched to the world</a>. Keep an eye out for our &#8216;bundle-a-week&#8217; special via our new newsletter called&#8230; &#8220;<a href="http://us10.campaign-archive1.com/?u=5b9a020fcf797987098cc7bca&amp;id=e7874277f7">Not another Newsletter</a>&#8221; which is sent every week!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/">Layers 1.2.11 Has Just Dropped, Here&#8217;s Why You Should Update</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:96:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"4";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:42:"What’s In Store For Layers in early 2016";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 05 Jan 2016 13:09:11 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Development";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"layers updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2147";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:394:"<p>The new year is already well underway at Layers HQ as we ramp up for an exciting 2016 with a packed development schedule focused on the Layers core.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/">What&#8217;s In Store For Layers in early 2016</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Vail Joy";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3832:"<p>We had such an overwhelmingly positive response to <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/">Layers Pro</a> in the few short months it has been growing, and have several crazy-cool ideas for how to make it even more perfect. However, we know the furniture still gets wet if there is a hole in the roof and we want to ensure Layers is the best it can be, always. That&#8217;s why it will be receiving our full attention in the first quarter of 2016. Below is a peek at some of the things we will be looking at in-depth:</p>\n<h3>Onboarding</h3>\n<p>User friendliness is Layers primary feature. When you jump in for the first time, our setup wizard helps you along with basic configurations and video examples of using the customizer. Interface improvements, updated content and a variety of beautiful new presets are on the way to spice up the Layers Dashboard and onboarding process to delight you right into your next website project.</p>\n<h3>SEO</h3>\n<p>WordPress is already built to be extremely effective at SEO without much more effort than turning on permalinks, but when it comes to pages on your site, you&#8217;re at a disadvantage. Google already tends to rank your internal content higher when building search engine results due to its denser keywords &#8211; ignoring dynamic pages created from templates as those pages themselves actually contain no content and duplicate information from other pages on your site. This can make home page optimization tough!</p>\n<p>SEO is a top development priority for us in the coming months, and will include an overhaul of the HTML structure in the theme templates to ensure the HTML5 outline of your pages is optimal and up to 2016 standards.</p>\n<h3>Page Revisions</h3>\n<div id="attachment_2152" style="width: 1000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2152"><img class="wp-image-2152 size-full" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha.png" alt="history-alpha" width="990" height="374" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha.png 990w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha-300x113.png 300w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha-768x290.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 990px) 100vw, 990px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Alpha version of our new page history feature</p></div>\n<p>Using the revisions API you&#8217;ll soon be able to roll back to a previous version of your page should you not be happy with your changes or if your server experiences any unwanted issues. The aim here is piece of mind <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/72x72/1f642.png" alt="🙂" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>\n<h3>Performance</h3>\n<p>WordPress 4.4 <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/" target="_blank">introduced big improvements</a> to the Customizer in both use and performance, but with every big change always comes a little gremlin to make something else act out. We will be going in with flamethrowers in the coming weeks to flush out these annoyances and make the Layers customization experience smoother than ever before.</p>\n<p>Have Something You Want In Layers Not Listed Here?</p>\n<p>We love hearing from you on how you are using Layers and what features you would like to see and welcome you to submit feature requests on our <a href="http://docs.layerswp.com/forums/" target="_blank">Layers Community site.</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/">What&#8217;s In Store For Layers in early 2016</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"6";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"Ending 2015 With Big Updates to Layers Pro, StoreKit and Two Of Our Themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:100:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:109:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 10 Dec 2015 20:26:25 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"layers pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2107";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:421:"<p>Overall the response to Layers Pro has been incredible so we wanted to keep the momentum and make it even better.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/">Ending 2015 With Big Updates to Layers Pro, StoreKit and Two Of Our Themes</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"David Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6765:"<h3>Let&#8217;s start with Layers Pro</h3>\n<p>Overall the response to Layers Pro has been incredible so we wanted to keep the momentum and make it even better.</p>\n<p>So with a big focus on serving you, our most valued users, we are happy to announce some big improvements:</p>\n<h4><strong>Background Videos</strong></h4>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/background-video.gif" rel="attachment wp-att-2119"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2119" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/background-video.gif" alt="background-video" width="640" height="300" /></a></p>\n<p>Finally Background videos are a possibility in Layers, allowing you to make bold visual statements when users enter your site.</p>\n<h4><strong>Social Widget</strong></h4>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2118"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2118" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1.png" alt="social-icons-widget" width="1100" height="314" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1.png 1100w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1-300x86.png 300w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1-768x219.png 768w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1-1024x292.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px" /></a></p>\n<p>This widget took much longer to developer than expected but it was for good reason. Our focus on UX is obsessive and we refused to release our Social Icon Widget until it was as intuitive as possible. We believe we have achieved that with global link inputs, widget and menu selection as well as the normal settings you&#8217;ve come to expect from Layers &#8211; including button coloring and sizing.</p>\n<h4><strong>Search in the Header</strong></h4>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-2113"><img class="size-full wp-image-2113 aligncenter" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up.jpg" alt="search-pop-up" width="1100" height="790" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up.jpg 1100w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up-300x215.jpg 300w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up-768x552.jpg 768w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up-1024x735.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px" /></a></p>\n<p>With Layers Pro you can now add a search button to the header of your site using a simple checkbox. When turned on, a search icon will appear inline with your menu and reveals a beautifully animated popup interface to search in.</p>\n<h4><strong>Header Background Image</strong></h4>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-2111"><img class="size-full wp-image-2111 aligncenter" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background.jpg" alt="header-background" width="1100" height="488" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background.jpg 1100w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background-300x133.jpg 300w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background-768x341.jpg 768w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background-1024x454.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px" /></a></p>\n<p>Layers Pro introduced deeper header customization and to make that even better we’re introducing header background image uploading.</p>\n<p>Last but not least we&#8217;ve added a <strong>Body Color Selector</strong> and improved <strong>Menu Styling</strong> which included hover states!</p>\n<p>If you don’t have Layers Pro yet, <a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/layers-pro-extended-customization-for-layers/11225042?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20Layers%20Pro%201.2">get it now for $25</a></p>\n<h3><b>StoreKit Updates</b></h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-2112"><img class="size-full wp-image-2112 aligncenter" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down.jpg" alt="header-cart-drop-down" width="1100" height="600" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down.jpg 1100w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down-300x164.jpg 300w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down-768x419.jpg 768w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down-1024x559.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/storekit-woocommerce-for-layers/11223808?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20StoreKit%201.6">StoreKit</a> has served as the backbone to the most valuable ecommerce functionality available for Layers. This week we’ve launched an update which adds a Header Mini Cart as well as new filters to the product widget including the ability to show only items on sale or only featured items.</p>\n<h3><b>Two new themes</b></h3>\n<p>If that wasn’t enough we also focused on getting two new themes out the gates before the end of 2015. They’re called Acquire 2.0 and Concept Living…</p>\n<p>Concept Living, announced a few weeks ago, is part of a strategy to bring some of our best selling themes onto the Layers platform &#8211; find out more about the <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/concept-living-layers-woocommerce-theme/5388303?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20Concept%20Living">Furniture theme</a> here.</p>\n<p>Acquire 2.0 is a big update of one of the first ever Layers themes. We decided to give it a more comprehensive design along with more page templates to choose from. Check out the demo or go directly to the <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/acquire-wordpress-corporate-theme/11220959?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20Acquire%202.0">business theme</a> to find out more.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/">Ending 2015 With Big Updates to Layers Pro, StoreKit and Two Of Our Themes</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:105:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"5";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:4:"href";s:29:"http://www.layerswp.com/feed/";s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";a:2:{s:12:"updatePeriod";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"hourly";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:15:"updateFrequency";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:"type";i:128;s:7:"headers";a:17:{s:4:"date";s:29:"Fr